    "The approach presented here requires no inputs other than the protein sequence and learns its characterized embedding using the statistics-informed graph convolutional networks.",
    "We show that EVCs and RCs have crucial effects on the predictions of protein function annotations and on the identifications of residues at functionally relevant sites.",
    "Our method produces high-accuracy annotations and identifies functional sites at the residue level.",
    "Therefore, this approach is well-suited for gaining a better understanding of the biological activities of unannotated or poorly studied proteins, as well as for quantitatively investigating the effects of disease-related variants.",
    "When evaluating the performance of the methods presented (see Fig. 3), it becomes evident that PhiGnet outperforms its counterparts due to its distinctive amalgamation of two key factors."
